Key Match Events: Georges Mikautadze scored the first goal of the match with a penalty on the stroke of half-time
Patrik Schick equalised for Czech Republic with a bundled goal from a corner
Georgia had a missed chance to win the game in the final minutes
Post-Match Reflections: Czech Republic's Vladimir Coufal was named the player of the match
Both teams remain in contention for qualification with a match to go
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at the Volksparkstadion in Euro 2024 Group F
Georgia complete their group stage with a match against Portugal, while Czech Republic play Turkey
Others: The draw leaves both teams on one point, having played two matches
Portugal and Turkey are on three points each
